I want to be clear: whether you have a big body or a small body, it is a good body. But that’s not the issue here: Plus size people have been fighting for inclusivity for a very long time, and it’s no where near inclusive yet. If someone who is straight sized claims they are “midsized” and tries to act like they are oppressed in the fashion world, it dilutes the voices that ACTUALLY need to be heard. So please, PLEASE, stop claiming you’re midsized if you are a size M or L. Midsized is traditionally someone who is too fat for straight sizes and too skinny for plus sizes. If you are a size M/L, you have absolutely no oppression when it comes to finding clothes that fit you. All retailers carry your size!! Please stop trying to latch onto the size inclusivity movement and make it about you. It’s not about you. Let the actual plus size and midsize people speak out and try to change the fashion industry. #sizeinclusive #plussizefashion #midsizefashion #plussize #midsize #sizeinclusivity #sizeinclusivefashion #plussizetiktok #bodypositivity

I know all of you also think this TikTok lawsuit is the most ridiculous thing you’ve ever witnessed, right. So here’s what we are going to do: 1. If this app gets banned, download a VPN and connect to another country and use the app 2. We need to vote out every single one of these people that are arguing to ban tiktok, regardless of if it gets banned or not. They dont deserve to be reps anymore for their stupidity. 3. We are going to write, call and tweet everyone in our government to get it together and threaten them that they will lose their jobs. 4. We need to delete instagram and facebook and be done with them. Period. We are now going to tank Meta… they deserve it and more. #tiktokban #meta #congresstiktokviralsong #congresstiktokban
